Malaysia Stocks: AirAsia, IJM, KNM, Malaysian Air, Transmile

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-02-24T09:16:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/malaysia-stocks-dayang-enterprise-knm-group-lion-transmile.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. close in Kuala
Lumpur.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI  Index fell 21.24, or 1.4
percent, to 1,489.87, lowest close since Dec. 1.  Airlines:  Malaysian Airline System Bhd . (MAS MK) and  AirAsia Bhd . (AIRA MK) dropped on concern fuel costs will
increase as oil prices climbed for a sixth day. Malaysian
Airline declined 6 percent to 1.88 ringgit, the most since March
2, 2010. AirAsia slumped 5.2 percent to 2.35 ringgit, the lowest
close since Nov. 12.  IJM Corp. (IJM MK), a construction, property and plantation
group, dropped 4 percent to 6 ringgit, the lowest close since
Dec. 3. The stock was cut to “hold” from “buy” at Maybank
Investment Bank Bhd. after IJM reported third-quarter earnings
that were “below expectations,” according to a report today.    KNM Group Bhd . (KNMG MK), an oil and gas services provider,
tumbled 14 percent to 2.43 ringgit, the steepest drop since Oct.
24, 2008, after saying its fourth-quarter profit more than
halved to 20.6 million ringgit ($6.8 million) on lower sales.       Lion Corp. (LION MK), a steel producer and builder, slid 10
percent to 31.5 sen, the largest slide since April 27, 2009. The
company said it had a loss of 98.6 million ringgit in the second
quarter ended Dec. 31 compared with a profit of 26.8 million
ringgit a year earlier as sales dropped.        Transmile Group Bhd . (TGB MK), an air-freight operator,
plunged 56 percent to 9 sen, a record low. The stock exchange
said the shares will be de-listed on March 7 after the company
failed to submit a plan to restore its finances on time,
according to a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
